Sentencas: High-temperature proton conductors are promising electrolytes for protonic solid oxide fuel cells (H+-SOFCs).
Titulo: Zirconium doping effect on the performance of proton-conducting BaZryCe0.8-yY0.2O3-δ (0.0 ≤ y ≤ 0.8) for fuel cell applications

Sentencas: In this study, the relationship between the Zr doping content and structure, chemical stability, carbon dioxide resistivity, sinterability and electrochemical properties of BaZryCe0.8-yY0.2O3-delta (BZCYy), 0.0 <= y <= 0.8, are studied systemically using XRD, CO2-TPD, SEM.

Sentencas: Zr doping suppresses carbonate formation, CO2-TPD demonstrates that the formative rate of carbonate over BZCYy are 7.50 x 10(-6) and 8.70 x 10(-7) mol m(-2) min(-1) at y = 0.0 and 0.4, respectively.
